		<p>I’ve finally (albeit weeks later than intended) created a primer on linear gradients with CSS. It’s a shallow dip into the deep pool of CSS gradients, but it’ll help get you started on taking advantage of gradients with Webkit, Firefox and even Internet Explorer! (Yes, really.)</p>
<p>It’s posted <a title="Link to Making the Grade: A Primer on Linear Gradients by Kyle Weems of Mindfly Web Design Studio" href="http://mindfly.com/blog/post/2010/02/26/Making-the-Grade-A-Primer-on-Linear-Gradients.aspx" target="_blank">over here</a> at Mindfly Web Design Studio. If you’re curious about gradients but scared of the syntax, check it out.</p>

