		<p class="preamble">The way most people link CSS intended for different media types, such as screen, print, or handheld, is to use multiple files. The files are then linked either through <code>link</code> elements with a <code>media</code> attribute or through <code>@import</code> statements with one or more media types specified.</p>
<p>There is nothing wrong with splitting your CSS into multiple files and linking them this way (I currently do that here on this site), but there are two drawbacks: it leads to more HTTP requests from the browser to the server and the need to maintain multiple CSS files.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.456bereastreet.com/archive/201002/css_efficiency_tip_use_a_single_stylesheet_file_for_multiple_media/">Read full post</a></p>
