		<p class="preamble">The W3C Working Group Note <a href="http://www.w3.org/TR/2009/NOTE-xhtml-media-types-20090116/">XHTML Media Types - Second Edition</a> contains updated guidelines for the use of different media types with XHTML documents – <code>text/html</code> vs. <code>application/xhtml+xml</code>. The note is about a year old now, so this will be old news to some readers. Better late than never, I suppose.</p>
<p>The document is now more focused on the <code>text/html</code> vs. <code>application/xhtml+xml</code> media types and includes <a href="http://www.w3.org/TR/2009/NOTE-xhtml-media-types-20090116/#compatGuidelines">Compatibility Guidelines</a> for ensuring that documents can work with either media type.</p>
