		<div>
<p>We are getting a little better at this iteration stuff. Opera 10 was released in September and now <a href="http://my.opera.com/desktopteam/blog/2009/12/22/from-all-of-us-to-all-of-you" title="From all of us to all of you">we are releasing</a> the first public build of Opera 10.5. Yay Desktop Team! <a href="http://foolip.org/">Philip</a> was on vacation so the HTML5 media elements (i.e. <code>video</code> and <code>audio</code>) are not yet in, but CSS transformations and transitions are. Hopefully we get this to final soon as it is a major improvement not just in standards support, but also in usability and speed. (And also so we get to try it on Ubuntu!)</p>
</div>

